The UDM wants the court to give Parliament the go-ahead to allows MPs to vote in secret during a motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma. JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court is delivering its ruling on the United Democratic Movement (UDM) s application to allow for a secret ballot in Parliament.The UDM approached the court last month, asking it to give Parliament the go ahead to allow MPs to vote in secret during a proposed motion of no confidence against President Jacob Zuma.WATCH: Constitutional Court rules on UDM's secret ballot application